social_posts.post_text: Running away is sometimes exactly what the soul needs. It’s important to know there’s so much out there outside of oneself, feeling small is sometimes exactly the medicine we need. Tokyo is somewhere I’ve always dreamt to go, I manifested this. If you went to my talk a few months back I said I would and I did, crazy how things align. So fortunate to have been able to experience Japan’s  magic, and connect with some amazing  people while there. Thanks so much for the hospitality and for making my dreams of painting in Japan reality @yoshi_travel_ @wallternatives_japan

Osaka, Japan 🇯🇵 thank you so much @wallshare for having us.  Really appreciate you and had so much fun with you.  For the books. This piece is about sharing our happiness with people, what is the point of happiness if you can’t enjoy it with loved ones. The secret to keeping happiness is to share it. 
Often times we are so isolated in our goals but ultimately we are all seeking the same thing, we’re all looking for acceptance and love from our community. Everything we do revolves around love, from the moment we get up and get dressed in the morning to the choices that we make throughout the day ,  how beautifully vulnerable that is. You can learn so much from others and their stories and how wonderful it is to exist in this moment and be able to experience this together. To share our moments of lows and highs and be able to be here to uplift one another. So if you havent, go smile at a stranger,ya never know who needs it. 
This lil Maria was inspired by my beautiful homegirl @jen4romtheblock 😌
But the answers you seek will never be found at home. Japan in 1 min. Thank you 🥹💖
Anotha day in the life. Viva Chucho 🇲🇽 All I want outta life is to do exactly what I wanna do with my time, what a beautiful life.

Life is about balance, in order to rebuild sometimes you must destroy. In order to grow sometimes you need to crack. In order for  good, there needs to be bad. And in order to breed new life there must be death. Life is about balance. It’s a beautiful chaotic system that harmoniously works it’s undertones into our journeys and keeps us grounded. Without knowing what it is to suffer, we wouldn’t understand or appreciate the light. The glistening sun rays peaking out of the clouds after the rain would be overlooked. 
I often paint these metaphors of car crashes because my life came to a crashing point before I was able to fully enjoy it. It was a car crash that actually led me here. I had left my job as a teacher and was painting murals, underpaid and knocking door to door in order to land any work via day and  using Lyft at night - the ride sharing  company to make ends meet. It was an acceptable system, it got me by, one day I got rear ended to the point that my car was taken from me and I had to scramble to figure out a plan, that was when my security blanket was ripped away and I had to make it work with just painting. I felt naked, I felt frustrated but it was the moment I needed to be standing face to face with one option, and to make that option work or to sink. somehow, someway with the fire burning in my heart I did make it work, and have been painting murals full time ever since. 
It took me a lot to get to that point, to be that brave, many obstacles led me down here, to realize I didn’t want to live a life without passion, that I was drowning in addiction and depression trying to find escapes  because I had so much unused passion and I didn’t know what to do with it. So I always remember when the hard times come, that I have the choice whether to let them suffocate  me or to become stronger by treading the water towards a new chapter. 

This picture was taken on my cell from the legendary @estevanoriol , we worked on a little doc that will be released later! Can’t wait to share that. That’s all for now ❤️🌱

Last one of 2022, considering I thought we were entering 2024 I think I am ready for 2023 🤣 I remember sitting in my moms basement drinking apple cider as a little girl as the clock struck midnight on 2000, had no idea what was to come, the challenges, and the triumphs. I questioned if the world would blow up and how everyone was going to dress in hyper galactic latex from that point forward.  Glad to say 23 years later our rock is still floating above the universe, latex is only for the moments to express our fierceness and not mandatory , and that I’ve grown and matured and learned so much about love, life and business. 
I’ve learned about heart break, death, about the unjustices of the world, learned to love people I had to let go of or that were taken away, learned that even I, can sink to the bottom but in turn was able to learn to get rid of judgement, learn empathy and understanding, and that I had the strength to climb out and over that Rapunzel braid into my castle and fairytale that I have created for myself. 
I learned about the power that comes from my choices and the impacts my actions can make, good or bad and I’ve learned that I’ll always keep learning and that the moment I don’t I will be ready to leave my earthly chapter. 
As little girls we were always taught that a handsome prince would come rescue us, but the sooner you realize that you are your own prince, that only you have the power to rescue yourself,  the moment you cut ties with the idea of someone or somethings arrival saving you is the moment you are set  free. 

Happy New Years thank you so much for all your constant support, for letting me continue to live out my dreams of painting and telling our stories through my art, thank you for loving and respecting me. Thank you for making me feel heard. I love you and forever grateful and without the support from my community I’d never be here today. Much love, enjoy your night and stay safe ! And remember 2023 is here- what do you want out of life ? You deserve it, show up for yourself from this point forward. Thank you @misteralek for this wall and thank you to everyone who’s supported my journey eternally grateful❤️

Buried emotions @thinkspace_art 
I’ve always done what I do as some sort of avenging  for everything that went wrong and all the bad things and fucked up people  that happened to that little girl I once was. I buried so many emotions, tried to numb them, tried to make them not exist to successfully avenge her and make her proud. I think externally it worked. As of today, I get to paint pictures for money on walls, that’s comical in itself. To have constantly gotten lectured as that little girl  for doodling instead of listening to lectures of old white dead men I had no connection to. The nagging voices that I’d never be anything have been silenced and I get to paint walls with a grin on my face. 
There’s something fucking poetic about it. 
I’ve always said life isn’t successful if you don’t live many lives in one, think my biggest fear is to be stuck in one, because I’ve had such a variety of horribly, crazy, good, insane, happy ones that to be stuck in one seems like such a disservice to the adventure that awaits, or perhaps that’s me making excuses, always wanting to be a wanderer. Perhaps that’s me afraid to ever grow up, knowing I’ll never be able to return. 
One thing that’s struck me lately is that time is ticking, this obsession isn’t new, with piles of artwork of different variations of clocks and our doom that have stacked up in piles overtime.
I’m  trying to come to terms with it. I use to be more open to the idea of it, when I hated my life the idea brought me peace but I’m in a different place, I want to be alive, not just get by. Im tired of piling and burying my emotions and using those as mountains to climb. They’ve taken me far, they’ve fueled me, but they aren’t sturdy enough to hold up through time. 
I want to dig through those emotions, I want to finally understand. I want to come to terms, I want to stop giving my demons a home on a canvas or a wall, I want to face them; I want to understand them, so I can say goodbye to them, I want to create mountains, not of suppressed emotions but of sustainability, of strength and resilience, not because I’m trying to distract myself but because I’m trying to face myself. This year will be the year.

“The escape” 
Chucho stole the donkey. Might not be a very good lesson to teach y’all  but you see, I’ve always rooted for the underdog. 
The one no one believed in. 
The underdog has an strong advantage though, he is unique. 
His only fault could be found only in himself, if he lets the world make him believe his uniqueness is a curse. 

Don’t let the world make you run from your greatness, let it make you run towards it.  Special thanks to  @thinkchulavista @firestoneauto for making this project possible

Don’t let anyone make you feel small!!!!! The Maria’s are constantly messin with Chucho, they’re so much smaller then him but always get one over on him! It’s a little recipe  made up of smarts, that fierce girl power, a lil bit a plotting, sugar and spice and all things nice PLUS the little fact that Chuchos a piñata, so he’s pretty accepting of the beatings he gets from the world. Isn’t it just a lil silly considering he completely towers over them, ah chuch when will you see how big and magnificent you truly are ? 

Thank you SO much  @olboy_melon @woes for being so helpful and gracious on my trip and making this wall possible. Much love Hawaii! Til next time. Mahalo 🤙🌺❤️

Happy Valentine’s Day. My imagination has been my love in this lifetime, it’s never failed me even when the world did. It always offered me a place of safety, of understanding and acceptance to be me. It’s taken me to places I couldn’t even dream of.  It’s given me the ability to live my life in the most free , chaotic but true way, to be on a journey of self discovery and to be encouraged to learn about myself by spending time day dreaming and playing with the thoughts in my head like pawns on a game board.  I challenge my mind every single day in order to  create a world for the world , that lives solely in my head and in my head only. I feel fortunate that through my art,  people can peak inside my mind, that people can relate to my mind, and for once in my life, it makes me feel truly understood.

I’ve been in this terrible place, I can’t seem to escape from , stuck inside my mind. Healing is a long journey. Lately I feel like I’ve found myself like a fly tangled within the weaves of problems, disillusions, unrealistic expectations I’ve created for myself, unable to break free. 
Im so used to grasping on to people, or things, or substances that can help me avoid, until I reach a point where I forget enough to move forward, but the garden of my mind is so overflowing with weeds that I can’t seem to see the flowers anymore. It’s impossible to find a way out. 

I can’t choose to bury anymore, the soil is cracking, filled at it’s capacity. It’s not safe to grow here anymore. 
Sometimes we reach this point in life, where there’s no where to escape to anymore. These moments are so hard to face, but it means there’s going to be a break through, a painful but beautiful realization waiting ahead. 

I’ve been good at learning acceptance of the things I can’t change but what I really need is a deeper understanding of the things led me here, to dig deeper, beyond the roots and into the darkness to find the answers that I know have been waiting to see the light. They deserve to be tended to, because after all, my flowers sprouted from this dirt, from this chaos.

“The escape”
Commissioned by the City of Chula Vista for Firestone.

Looking inward and realizing that even though the world is not a  just place, that the bigger problem, or the bigger solution isn’t the way the world is, but how we choose to react to it.

It is the reason why some of us find happiness and others do not. 

Happiness is a choice we often forget we have the power to make. 

We can’t necessarily change the world today, but we can change our reactions towards it. 

Every interaction we have with one another are true reflections of self so we all perceive things differently, experience things differently. One story from  different perspectives becomes a multitude of stories, not from the basis of deceit but the the basis of different perceptions that make us unique. From a place of collected experiences, from the true reflections of self. 
 

Face to face you’ll always be, and the reflection will always be yours. 

Time is of the essence. 

It was an honor to be invited to Vegas to create this mural for @lamonarosalv @building180

Peace and growth, over everything. I’ve battled so much in my life with my own self and this trip couldn’t have come at a better time. Painting takes a lot from you, you essentially leave a little piece of your soul everywhere you paint. It’s always been a magnetic draw, to somehow be able to escape in real time, almost like you disappear into the wall for a bit and then you step back and there’s the world you created staring back at you. So blessed to have that, we all need escapes from reality some times. Happy my escapes have turned into tangible creations, like you all get to peak inside my mind, in this case, inside my living room 👀 Rain, shine, violent storms, whatever life throws my way, I have had too many low moments in my life to not accept and understand I can get through them all , and in fact they make me a better artist, and human being so I am grateful for the lows too. Much love to @worldwidewalls family for including me and to  all the beautiful people I met.

While building relationships is amazing and crucial, people are bound to let you down. 

The most important relationship you can build is with yourself. 
And you should put the most weight and value into that. 

Take it from me, your imagination can take you to places you’ve never dreamed of. 

Stop waiting for people. 
Go do all those things you’ve been wanting to do
Your friend canceled on the trip? Can’t make it to dinner after all? You really want to go to the gym but no one to go with? 
GO ANYWAYS !! 

The story book we need is to teach the youth that you are your own Prince Charming, you are responsible for the life you lead, how powerful is that?! So learn to value your own company. Sit with your imagination, write it out, create it. Love yourself enough. You deserve it. 
 
And I promise the world will be better for it. 
🫶🫶🫶🫶 thanks to @cityofnationalcity for letting us film this at the fair at Kimball park this past weekend. Special thanks to @riot_juan

The dance between good and evil. The battle between our own selves to deeper understand what is right for us and for others, we have no previous life time to compare our choices to so we are often times left  feeling vulnerable in figuring things out to the best of our abilities, feeling clueless but trying our best to find the  solutions, and sometimes ( and naturally) we are left feeling confused with our decisions, replaying scenarios hoping things went differently. That’s  life, it’s a balance of good and of bad, no one’s perfect, no one makes all the right decisions so be kind, offer yourself and others grace in dealing with scenarios in life you’ve never found yourself in. This dance of uncertainty is a dance we will forever find ourselves in, so get comfortable with the uncomfortable. The dance between life and death, between good and evil, the dance of balance, of uncertainties. ( life’s a dance party💃🏼💃🏼 ) One thing is certain though,  time is leaving, take that as you please, it may be negative or it may be the exact thing you need to hear to get your ass into gear. Let’s live this lifetime, let’s dance, let’s fall, let’s get back up, but let’s live to the best of our abilities because  I refuse to dance the dance of regret for the things I did not do.  #callyourmom  Thanks again for the opportunity to paint this @thinkspace_art it was such a fun project and special thanks to  @halopigg for your help

The Butcher Block. I grew up in here, frequently coming to get my fix of all the dulces Mexicanos and visiting my abuelitos. This is my families business in the center of Barrio Logan. If this year taught me anything it is that there will forever be a constant ebb and flow.  I’ve experienced some of the highest highs this year, but in the same token I’ve also experienced  some of the lowest lows. It’s a rollercoaster we are sentenced to ride until we depart. 

This mural is representative of a doorway, a portal for lack of a better word, to the past. To our past experiences, the people we once knew and loved who disappeared from our path, to our ancestors and all those who came before whos names we’ve forgotten An acknowledgment to their sacrifices and mistakes that opened the door for us, that lead us to this very moment. A tip of the hat for all the forgotten. It’s an understanding that we all have a door, a story, that started long before we arrived. Were so comfortable closing doors to make room for the new but those doors sometimes creak open and leave a glowing trail of the past shining through. A compilation of experiences that make you you.

Hi 
My names Michelle Ruby 
I’m a creator, survivor, artist, dreamer, mother. 
I like furry things. I don’t like to follow rules too much. But I am a fan of culture, of people, of their stories and connection. I like to see everyone as their own unique universe and that intrigues me. 
I like to run when I’m down, or just push my body physically, I find it really helps push away the darkness. I’ve found that in life the darkness always makes it’s way back; that’s the nature of life and the human experience, so finding a way to handle it is something I really recommend. 
I really enjoy creating things, it’s my way of expressing myself. I am still  always surprised people actually like what I create, but I’ll take it because it makes me feel like the jumble in my mind might be more then just jumble. 
I hope everyone is doing well and finding happiness, I know it’s a constant search but I hope you all find what you’re looking for, and I hope you remember you won’t find it in any place  else but inside you my friend. 
Con mucho amor siempre. G2G

Siempre en mi corazón. 
To our brothers and sisters who left us, we still feel your presence and it will impact us forever. 
I hope that wherever you are, you never forget how special you are, how loved you are, and how much you’re forever missed. Spending Dia de Los muertos in Michoacán was a life changing experience. 
This mural was inspired by my visits to the graves, the presence of the living celebrating the lives of those who passed on to the next, the sounds of the banda, and laughter of the family and friends celebrating what once was in the physical form, but what will forever be in our hearts. 
Death is the next chapter. 
America makes death so taboo, but it will always remain an unspoken truth waiting to be told. Death is a part of all of our stories and if we found a way to acknowledge it’s presence then we may just  free ourselves from all we fear.
